## 2. Celery Task Execution Detail

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant SCH as APScheduler
    participant RED as Redis (Broker)
    participant CW as Celery Worker
    participant TASK as run_scraper()
    participant ASYNC as _run_scraper_async()
    participant PG as PostgreSQL
    participant SCRAPER as BaseScraper subclass
    participant GOV as Govt Website

    SCH->>RED: run_scraper.delay(source_id)<br/>serialize to JSON message
    RED->>CW: Dequeue task message
    CW->>TASK: Execute run_scraper(source_id)
    TASK->>ASYNC: _run_async(_run_scraper_async())
    Note over TASK,ASYNC: Creates new asyncio event loop<br/>Runs coroutine synchronously

    ASYNC->>PG: SELECT Source WHERE id = source_id
    PG-->>ASYNC: Source row

    ASYNC->>PG: INSERT ScraperRun (started_at)
    ASYNC->>ASYNC: _get_scraper_instance(source)<br/>Lookup SCRAPER_REGISTRY[source.scraper_module_name]

    ASYNC->>SCRAPER: scraper.fetch()
    SCRAPER->>GOV: safe_get(url)<br/>curl_cffi + random UA + retry × 3
    GOV-->>SCRAPER: HTML/PDF response
    SCRAPER-->>ASYNC: List[RawDocument]

    loop For each RawDocument
        ASYNC->>PG: SELECT Document WHERE source_id AND url
        alt Document exists
            ASYNC->>ASYNC: Compare content_hash
            alt Hash changed
                ASYNC->>PG: UPDATE Document (hash, raw_text, status=FETCHED)
                ASYNC->>RED: process_document.delay(doc_id)
            else Hash same
                Note over ASYNC: Skip (no change)
            end
        else New document
            ASYNC->>PG: INSERT Document (status=FETCHED)
            ASYNC->>RED: process_document.delay(doc_id)
        end
    end

    ASYNC->>PG: UPDATE Source (last_fetched_at, consecutive_failures=0)
    ASYNC->>PG: UPDATE ScraperRun (success=True, counts)
    ASYNC->>PG: COMMIT
    ASYNC-->>CW: Return result dict
```

