## 5. Celery Task Configuration

| Task Name | Function | Max Retries | Retry Delay | Rate Limit | Binds |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| `regradar.run_scraper` | `run_scraper` | 1 | 600s | — | ✓ |
| `regradar.process_document` | `process_document` | 2 | 60s | 50/hour | ✓ |
| `regradar.generate_alerts` | `generate_alerts_for_item` | 2 | 120s | — | ✓ |
| `regradar.deliver_alert` | `deliver_alert_task` | 3 | 300s | — | ✓ |

All tasks use `_run_async()` helper to bridge sync Celery with async SQLAlchemy/service code.
